      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ANGRY CHIEF (1) had been racing in honest fashion recording two placings in a row before finishing fourth (27.45) at Horsham latest. Form at the trip sound including three wins. Has won four of nine starts from this draw. Can discover winning form. REGAL BARRY (4) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (30.63) at this track behind Bun Quake in a Grade 5. Stalked the pace but found the line strongly. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Expected to feature. SIR DODGE (7) scored (38.06) last time out over 595m at Angle Park five months ago. Form at the trip sound including eight wins. Looks well placed here and has the ability. Go well. WYONG HOUSTON (3) has strong credentials at this circuit over this journey.",
